    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "That's a good start. You mentioned that proponents are trying to \"ensure\" low-income communities aren't hit hardest, but I've seen a lot of people arguing that it's basically just a tax on people who can't afford to live in the city or work from home. Do you think those concerns are valid, or are they just being used to stall progress?",
